Clicks has committed to spend more money with small businesses, and support local beauty and hair brands. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Small Business Development Minister Khumbudzo Ntshavheni says she's encouraging Unilever to stock more African hair products from small businesses. Ntshavheni has reached an agreement with Clicks that it will do the same. Clicks received backlash over an advert that compared black hair unfavourably to white hair. READ: TRESemmé apologises for Clicks ad Earlier this week, the minister rejected Clicks' apology. The beleaguered retailer has now met with Ntshavheni after the offensive advert uproar. Clicks has also committed to spending more money with small businesses and support local beauty and hair brands.